products.title: LDT ETU V2 LITE (Mosfet) - Rear wired M4 Type
products.body_html:
Simple, effective and durable! the LDT EUT V2 Lite is a fantatsic entry level ETU.
Optical sensor for the sector gear, nice durable responsive trigger switch and easy to set up for the selector with a switch.

I has adaptive learning to recognize brushed or brushless motors, and intelligently adjust braking force to suit, to ensure a consistent piston position after cycling.

It features programmable fire modes, and mag prime off or durations up to 1.5 seconds.

The unit is conformal coated to resist against moisture and lubricants causing electrical issues. Also features Teflon coated silver-plated wiring.

  • LDT ETU V2 Lite
  • XT-30 battery connection
  • M4 magazine terminals 
  • Mounting screw and plastic washer
  • Motor Terminals


Warnings from the ETU


    

  • 2 beeps / 2 blue flashes: Battery low, needs charging or replacement.
    • 

  • 3 beeps / 3 blue flashes: Mainboard temperature high, needs cooling down.
    • 

  • 5 beeps / 5 blue flashes: Gear not detected/stuck or motor installation issue.
    • 

  • 
1 beep / 1 blue flash: Short circuit in the feeding mechanism.

    • 



 


Please note: If you are using a metal selector swivel, such as the A5 and PDW dual-sided selector, please apply a layer of electrical tape to the part that comes into contact with the fire control selector for insulation.

products.title: Solink Programming Card for V5 Brushless Motor
products.body_html:
SLC Lite digital programming card can adjust motor speed by 1k rpm increments and torque meanwhile also provides battery monitoring function.

Only for V5 Solink brushless motors.

SLC digital programming card Setup guideline :

Motor speed can be adjusted with 1k rpm increments with this digital programming card

***Digital programming card  only work with extra  V5 Brushless motor, not workable for our other models either other brands motor

The starting torque of the motor can be adjusted by current change. (Default value:60%)

Button Description:

M  Short press to select the item to be set, long press to quickly reconnect when disconnected from the motor.

–    Short press to decrease the value of the selected item, long press to quickly decrease the value of the selected item.

+  Short press to increase the value of the selected item, long press to quickly increase the value of the selected item.

S.  Long press to save the settings to the motor.

Attention! Safety precautions:

1)Some malfunctions, poor contact, or unexpected situations may cause the motor to rotate unexpectedly. Therefore, the motor must be securely fixed before using this product.

2)The motor must be reliably connected to the cable of the setting card before the setting card can be powered on, otherwise it may cause accidental rotation of the motor.

3)The battery voltage used to power the setting card must be higher than 7.4V, otherwise it may cause the motor to rotate unexpectedly.

4)After the settings are saved, the settings card will self-disconnect and disconnect from the motor. If you want to reset it, you must power it on again or press and hold the M button to reconnect.

5)While in the setting menu, do not disconnect the motor wires, otherwise it may cause the motor to rotate unexpectedly.

6)If the maximum current rating of the ETU is lower than the defined starting current of the motor,we are not responsible for the damage it might caused.

products.title: Solink Brushless Motor - V5 60k (Programmable)
products.body_html:
Experience the power and precision of the SOLINK Brushless Motor V5.

With the V5 Programming Board (sold separately) you can customize your RPM and torque for a dynamic range of performance. With the one-way bearing design, anti-release latch is not required in the gearbox. enjoy smoother operation and reduced maintenance of your airsoft or gel blaster. Elevate your gameplay and leave the competition in the dust!

Upgrades in the SOLINK V5 motor:

  1. With one-way bearing design, anti-release latch is no longer required in the gearbox. Get rid of the noise from the anti-release latch, gears turns smoother than ever in the gearbox.
  2. Programming RPM and level of Torque. Customise the motor for your upgrade needs, up to 60000 rpm.
  3. The single piece CNC frame and shaft provides a stronger base to immensely extend the lifespan of the motor.
  4. Faster start, less heat emitted, faster active break, lower energy consumption.

products.title: LDT LDX GEN3.0 CNC Assembled V2 Gearbox (30 RPS)
products.body_html:
The latest GEN 3.0 LDT LDX CNC Expert gearbox is ready to go for your next build! Pre-built by LDT with 18:1 CNC LDT gears and LDT Lite ETU.

These can support 30 rounds per second when paired with a motor matched to do so!

These are fantastic for converting blasters with troublesome gearboxes, or upgrading from a nylon gearbox.

Split design makes servicing the compression section and changing springs much easier.

These are a CNC 7075 aluminium

Features a 4 prong bearing spring retainer to keep the spring from diving and bending.

9mm bearings for smooth gear operation and longevity.

The new terminal block has locations for M4 and MP5 terminals, and features a channel for routing front wiring.

Includes:

  • Gearbox. Complete and assembled 
  • T-piece and barrel spring

Features

  • CNC 7075 aluminium shell
  • CNC 18:1 LDT gears (short stroked 2 teeth)
  • LDT V2 Lite ETU (mosfet)
  • Full metal rack piston
  • 4 prong bearing spring retainer 
  • LDT tappetless cylinder head
  • XT30 battery connection

Please note that the MP5K version has a 60% cylinder, bolt release has been ground off by factory, MP5 mag terminals, front wired, and the selector plate and trigger is M4 spec. If used on an LDT MP5 (non K model) please use MP5 trigger and selector plate! Could be used in an M4/416 front wired if the magazine terminals were changed to M4 style.

products.title: LDT LDX GEN3.0 Advanced Assembled V2 Gearbox
products.body_html:

The new terminal block has locations for M4 and MP5 terminals, and features a channel for routing front wiring.

Features
